title: England collapse caused by Wahab Riaz and Yasir Shah in second Test - News Shopper
text:
England collapsed to Wahab Riaz and Yasir Shah on the third morning of the second Test, to concede a yawning first-innings deficit in Dubai. But they were to falter alarmingly from 206 for three to 242 all out by lunch, handing Pakistan a mid-match advantage of 136 - on a pitch expected to increasingly favour spin and make England's task of batting last a daunting prospect.
 News Shopper.
